## _This is the sixth time I edit this page and it is always hard to write it in such way it would not require editing for long period of time because things change so fast._

My name is Georgi Mirchev, born on 09 November 1990 (you can calculate how old I am). I live in a country called Bulgaria and which I love a lot. You can find it in the south-eastern part of Europe and we are also part of the European Union. Currently, I work in our capital called Sofia, but I go to my home city very often to walk my two beagles.

I love programming and I am especially interested in code architecture and design patterns. Most of the time I write native Android code (mostly Kotlin) but I also use Javascript a lot. I have a lot of experience with Android apps – I have been programming for Android since version 2.2 was released. I really enjoy writing smart and useful apps. This includes the apps in my [Google Play profile](https://play.google.com/store/apps/developer?id=NMP) and in [GitHub](https://github.com/n0m0r3pa1n/). I have worked on many projects for different companies ( [a link to my LinkedIn profi](https://www.linkedin.com/in/georgi-mirchev-7b486665/) le). I have .NET experience more than 2 years and a half, some basic Python experience with Django and Flask, Javascript experience for more than 2 years with the rise of NodeJS.

I had a StartUp with my university colleagues where we made apps like [RetroSelfie](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.iovchev.selfieseditor) and AppHunt which are a real example how building apps for Android can let you support yourself without having to work for anyone. I read/listen to books a lot and mostly on topics like “clean code” or “personal improvement”, you can check my [Goodreads](https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/36345232-georgi-mirchev) account if you want to have a chat about books.

This blog was started with the purpose of sharing knowledge. I started it back in 2012 when I was getting involved in programming and I thought that I should share the problems I meet and how I solve them with the world around me. I love sharing knowledge, you can see in LinkedIn that a spent some time being a lecturer either at one of my companies or at a free course on Android development. So if you share this passion, let’s have a chat about it!

At the moment the most important thing for me is my family! I am a proud father of a girl and I recently switched from owning a motorcycle to owning a camper. I try to have time for everything but as every parent knows - time is more precious now than ever before.

If you want to have a chat with me, you can use the Social Contacts at the top of this page or just ping me an email:

gmirchev90@gmail.com

I also have [another blog](http://mirchev.space/) where I share my thoughts & trips, but this is a whole other topic. I hope you will enjoy what you find in this blog and it will inspire you to do more interesting things!
